        <title>Legislative Branch</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <section class="main-idea segment-opener" data-uuid="04de5a315bfb46edb3197dabaeba3f12">
            <article data-uuid="3325980a5b894e869216aeef0af479c7">
                <h4 data-uuid="fdc8677454d94206b3d41eac102c9019">Main Idea</h4>
                <p class="main-idea" data-uuid="886f7e7dac9c4fc9810735b6a73cb7eb">The legislative branch makes the nation’s laws.</p>
                <h2 data-uuid="5eea97c7e4e7484a9a40667fb7bcc964">Legislative Branch </h2>
                <div class="yellow-star-yellow-bar" data-uuid="ec7b994e14084d588a9b463098dfdc6f"></div>
            </article>
        </section>
        <p data-uuid="b9f816550dc945e6aa8cd838baeaf64c">Article I of the Constitution covers the legislative branch, or Congress. The legislators elected to Congress make the nation’s laws. Congress is divided into the House of Representatives and the Senate.</p>
        <section class="cause-effect" data-uuid="8e6ed806f2d245edaaccb5bc7bd04aa3">
            <article class="box" data-uuid="4270c8d58366470d92eee43a718d4091">
                <div class="header-element" data-uuid="cf5c5eafab0b4324929c921a1e60f2af">
                </div>
                <div class="quickfacts" data-uuid="52b1644c32f843f380e9cde279ba9412">
                    <h5 data-uuid="bcb95fcf9d7342d1898cd126e0fc5125">QUICK FACTS</h5>
                </div>
                <h2 data-uuid="d4879bcadc534c9a88bef9a353135773">Responsibilities of Congress</h2>
                <p data-uuid="f8bf90976f8147e293bfa5afcea0ba94">The main responsibility of the legislative branch, or Congress, is to make the nation’s laws.</p>
            </article>
        </section>
        <section class="table-pattern" data-uuid="00fcd018d60f4a699218917ee2e9bb8a">
